§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬continuous-time time-invariant linear dynamical system❭ is
    a tuple $(A, B, C, D)$ where $A ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$, $B ∈ 𝗥^{n
    × m}$, $C ∈ 𝗥^{k × n}$ and $D ∈ 𝗥^{k × m}$. ⦉

  ‖ Given an ❬input❭ $u: 𝗥 → 𝗥^m$, it models a ❬state❭ $x: 𝗥
    → 𝗥^n$ and ❬output❭ $y: 𝗥 → 𝗥^k$ by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \begin{aligned} ⦉

      ‖ \dot{x} ❲&❳= Ax + Bu, ᜶ ⦉

      ‖ y ❲&❳= Cx + Du. ⦉

      ‖ \end{aligned} ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ Here $Ax$ is called the ❬drift term❭ and $Bu$ is called
    the input term (of $\dot{x}$). ⦉
⦉

